D-FINE-cpp is a C++/TensorRT inference port of D-FINE
(https://github.com/Peterande/D-FINE), which is licensed under Apache-2.0.

The checkpoint exporter contains a detection-only model implementation derived
from D-FINE-seg (https://github.com/ArgoHA/D-FINE-seg) at revision
f5a46697b9c3c6dc435b6c86718cc18452ae9baf, Copyright 2026 The D-FINE-seg
Authors, licensed under Apache-2.0. D-FINE-seg incorporates D-FINE and RT-DETR
model code; their copyright notices are retained in the derived source files.

Parts of the runtime scaffolding were derived from rf-detr-cpp
(https://github.com/infracv/rf-detr-cpp), Copyright 2026 rf-detr-cpp
contributors, licensed under Apache-2.0: the TensorRT session wrapper,
CUDA RAII/check helpers, logging, the C ABI surface, the preprocessing
kernel core, and the CPU decode skeleton. All derived files carry
substantial D-FINE-specific modifications; see the per-file notices.

Bundled / vendored third-party components:
  - third_party/stb (stb_image) — public domain / MIT
  - nlohmann/json — MIT (fetched at build time)

This software links against NVIDIA TensorRT and NVIDIA CUDA, which are
proprietary NVIDIA SDKs. They are not distributed with this repository;
the user must install them separately.
